Raw Text:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1664
S.P. 658 In Senate, April 15, 2025
An Act to Repeal the Dirigo Business Incentives Program
Reference to the Committee on Housing and Economic Development suggested and
ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator TIPPING of Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3210-E, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. J, §4,
3 is further amended to read:
4 1. Discount rates. Transmission and distribution utilities may offer discounted rates
5 to qualified Pine Tree Development Zone businesses established under Title 30‑A and
6 qualified businesses with respect to the Dirigo business incentives program established
7 under Title 36, section 5219‑AAA. If a transmission and distribution utility requires
8 approval prior to offering any such rate, the transmission and distribution utility shall apply
9 to the commission in accordance with applicable provisions of this Title, and the
10 commission may approve the rate if it finds it to be in accord with applicable requirements
11 of this Title, except that the commission may take into account the overall benefits to
12 ratepayers resulting from state efforts to promote economic development.
13 Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §191, sub-§2, ¶SSS, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. J, §7, is
14 repealed.
15 Sec. 3. 36 MRSA §5219-AAA, as amended by PL 2023, c. 631, §2, is repealed.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill repeals the Dirigo business incentives program, which provides a tax credit to
1188 businesses that make eligible capital investments or provide qualified training to employees
1199 in certain business sectors.
